				I commend you on this article. Taking accountability shows integrity, but what about the patient? You barely mention that there was no lasting harm...and that's about it regarding the patient. How did your error affect him or her? I've been through a few surgeries, minor ones, and have felt trepidation in placing my full trust in them to do their best and not make mistakes. So far, so good. And I have to wonder how I would feel if one did make a mistake, even if there was no lasting harm. So you see, it's not only about YOU. The other side of the mistake should be addressed as well.			</div>
			
