			<div class="comment_body">
				<div class="comment_time">
					13 hours ago ( 3:46 PM)				</div>

																												
				Of course doctors will make mistakes, nurses, any human will error. In this case, thank goodness no permanent damage was done. <br />
<br />
But what we need to address is what happens to those who do have permanent damage from a doctor's error, a nurse's error or a corporation's error. My family is still suffering from a corporation's error. Faulty engineering producing a defective product has caused lifelong illness for us, medical costs are over 7 million to date (over a 12 yr period). We get no help from anyone. We've used up all of our savings, retirement, lost our home - everything is gone because we no longer have our health. We struggle to pay our ins premium every month and pray that we have enough for food. <br />
<br />
All the while the folks responsible for the lousy workmanship are still cashing their huge paychecks. <br />
<br />
Forgiveness is great, but try eating it. This country needs to do more for those, thru no fault of their own, have to live with the consequences of someone else's mistake.			</div>
			
